div.p:
The Prince’s countenance fell. “I don’t want a cloak, for I never go out.
                    Sometimes nurse hoists me on to the roof, and carries me round by the parapet;
                    but that is all. I can’t walk, you know, as she does.”

“Down, Snap, down: Stop that, or I’ll thrash you,” the Prince heard him say;
                    though with such a rough, hard voice and queer pronunciation that it was
                    difficult to make the words out. “Hollo! Let’s warm ourselves by a race.”
